<P>I &s;eated my&s;elf, and away the Dean walk|ed, or rather trolled,
as hard as ever he could drive. I could not help &s;miling at his odd Gait, for
I thought to my&s;elf, he had written to &s;o much in Prai&s;e of Hor&s;es,
that he was re&s;olved to imitate them as nearly as he could: As I was
indulging this Fancy, the Dean returned to me, and gave me a &s;trong
Confirmation of his Par|tiality to tho&s;e Animals; 
<Q REND="inline">'I have been con&s;idering, Madam, as I walked,
&s;aid he, what a Fool Mr. <HI>P&mdash;n</HI> was to marry you, for he could
