Three&s;core) you do not know what may have happened: Tho' I mu&s;t tell you,
you are very partial to her; for here I have not been acquainted with her above
&s;ix Months, and I have al|ready di&s;covered two intolerable Faults in her;
'tis true, I looked &s;harp, or per|haps they might have e&s;caped my No|tice:
Nay, Madam, do not look &s;ur|pri&s;ed, I am re&s;olved to tell your
Hu&s;|band, that he may break you of them.'</Q> 
<Q REND="inline">'Indeed, Sir, returned I, my Surprize is, that you
have not found out two and fifty in half that time; but let me know them, and I
will mend of them, if I can.'</Q> 
<Q REND="inline">'Well put in, &s;ays he, for I be|lieve you can't;
but eat your Dinner, however, for they are not capital.'</Q> I obeyed, yet was
very impatient to know my particular Errors; he told me, 
<Q REND="inline">'I &s;hould hear of them Time enough.'</Q></P>
<P><PB N="85" REF="92">The Things being taken away; 
